{"id":"b08bf6a0a59785ff72900a4a6873f25a9d7b2921","axis":"silent","repo":"aquasecurity/trivy","sha":"b08bf6a0a59785ff72900a4a6873f25a9d7b2921","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"docs/guide/coverage/others/seal.md","lines":["@@ -3,10 +3,14 @@"," !!! warning \"EXPERIMENTAL\"","     Scanning results may be inaccurate."," ","-While it is not an OS, this page describes the details of the [Seal Security]( https://sealsecurity.io/) vulnerability feed.","-Seal provides security advisories and patched versions for multiple Linux distributions, including [Debian](../os/debian.md), [Ubuntu](../os/ubuntu.md), [Alpine](../os/alpine.md), [Red Hat Enterprise Linux](../os/rhel.md), [CentOS](../os/centos.md), [Oracle Linux](../os/oracle.md), and [Azure Linux (CBL‑Mariner)](../os/azure.md).","+This page describes the details of the [Seal Security](https://sealsecurity.io/) vulnerability feed.","+Seal provides security advisories and patched versions for both OS packages and application dependencies."," ","-Seal advisories are used when Trivy finds packages that indicate Seal-provided components:","+## OS Packages","+","+Seal provides patched versions for multiple Linux distributions, including [Debian](../os/debian.md), [Ubuntu](../os/ubuntu.md), [Alpine](../os/alpine.md), [Red Hat Enterprise Linux](../os/rhel.md), [CentOS](../os/centos.md), [Oracle Linux](../os/oracle.md), and [Azure Linux (CBL‑Mariner)](../os/azure.md).","+","+Seal OS package advisories are used when Trivy finds packages that indicate Seal-provided components:"," "," - Packages whose name or source name starts with `seal-` (for example, `seal-wget`, `seal-zlib`)."," ","@@ -25,3 +29,19 @@ For details on supported scanners, features, and behavior for each base OS, refe"," - [Oracle Linux](../os/oracle.md)"," - [Azure Linux (CBL‑Mariner)](../os/azure.md)"," ","+## Application Dependencies","+","+Seal also provides patched versions of application dependencies with their own vulnerability advisories. Trivy automatically detects Seal-patched packages based on special naming patterns specific to each ecosystem.","+","+### Supported Ecosystems","+","+| Ecosystem | Package Pattern | Example |","+|-----------|----------------|---------|","+| Python (pip) | `seal-*` | `seal-requests` |","+| Node.js (npm) | `@seal-security/*` | `@seal-security/ejs` |","+| Go | `sealsecurity.io/*` | `sealsecurity.io/github.com/Masterminds/goutils` |","+| Java (Maven) | `seal.sp*` | `seal.sp1.org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-http` |","+| Ruby (RubyGems) | `seal-*` | `seal-rack` |","+","+When Trivy detects packages matching these patterns, it automatically uses Seal Security advisories for vulnerability scanning.","+"],"additions":23,"deletions":3,"truncated":false},{"path":"go.mod","lines":["@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@ require ("," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/bolt-fixtures v0.0.0-20200903104109-d34e7f983986"," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/go-gem-version v0.0.0-20201115065557-8eed6fe000ce"," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/go-npm-version v0.0.2","-\tgithub.com/aquasecurity/go-pep440-version v0.0.1","+\tgithub.com/aquasecurity/go-pep440-version v0.0.2-0.20260224065243-f9bba28c51a4"," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/go-version v0.0.1"," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/iamgo v0.0.10"," \tgithub.com/aquasecurity/table v1.11.0","@@ -73,7 +73,7 @@ require ("," \tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-disk v0.0.0-20260423015231-f7a470ebd472"," \tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-ebs-file v0.0.0-20260422020928-9d24e29aac27"," \tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-ext4-filesystem v0.0.0-20260423010602-fe51f5b5e52b","-\tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-mvn-version v0.0.0-20250131095131-f4974fa13b8a","+\tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-mvn-version v0.0.0-20260119054159-d21fcd2e7de1"," \tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-vmdk-parser v0.0.0-20260423020818-08305fa668d2"," \tgithub.com/masahiro331/go-xfs-filesystem v0.0.0-20260422061116-d21e5e4481bb"," \tgithub.com/mattn/go-shellwords v1.0.12"],"additions":2,"deletions":2,"truncated":false},{"path":"go.sum","lines":["@@ -159,8 +159,8 @@ github.com/aquasecurity/go-gem-vers